mxTextCell.label: Counter-Strike Global Offensive : Money earned by a team in a competitive game

mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label: In Counter-Strike Global Offensive, a competitive game can have a maximum of 30 rounds. The first team who reaches 16 rounds, wins the game.
mxTextCell.prevLabel: In Counter-Strike Global Offensive, a competitive game can have a maximum of 30 rounds. The first team who reaches 16 rounds, wins the game.

mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label: Players are divided in 2 teams Counter Terrorists (CT) and Terrorists (T)
mxTextCell.prevLabel: Players are divided in 2 teams Counter Terrorists (CT) and Terrorists (T)

mxTextCell.title: Text
mxTextCell.label:
In order to win a round, Counter Terrorists needs to either:

- Kill all the Enemies
- Time runs out without letting Terrorists plant the bomb
- Defuse the Bomb
